File: Mineral Resources and Energy Minister Gwede Mantashe. GCIS CAPE TOWN - Mineral Resources and Energy Minister, Gwede Mantashe says fuel prices are determined at the international level. He says South Africa imports crude oil and finished products at a price that is set on an international level. READ: LIVESTREAM: Parliament debate high fuel price increases Mantashe says there should be engagements on how financial relief to motorists can be reached as simple solutions will not last.